Double Crumb Apple Crisp
  --Carissa Shaw

5 lb Granny Smith apples, cored, peeled, and sliced into thin slices
1/2 c sugar
1 tsp lemon juice
3 tbsp cinnamon, divided
2 c quick oats
2 c brown sugar
1 c ap flour
1 c butter, softened

Preheat oven to 350F. In a large bowl, combine the apples, granulated sugar, lemon juice, and 2 tbsp of the cinnamon. In a second large bowl, combine the oats, brown sugar, flour, 1 tbsp of the cinnamon, and the butter. Mix until well combined and crumbly in texture. Pour half of the oat mixture into the bottom of a greased 10Ã—15" glass baking dish and pat it down evenly. Spread the apples over the oat mixture in the pan, then top with the remaining oat mixture. Bake the apple crisp for 45 min. Cool slightly before serving.




